params._bootstrapPrice: A price to be set as a bootstraping value for this block
params._numIdleRounds: The number of rounds an oracle must be idle (not participating) before a removal
params._oracleManager: The contract of the oracle manager.

isSubscribed(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

params._blockNumber: The blocknumber acting as nonce to prevent replay attacks.
params._coinpair: The coin pair to report (must match this contract)
params._sig_r: The array of R-component of Oracle signatures.
params._sig_s: The array of S-component of Oracle signatures.
params._sig_v: The array of V-component of Oracle signatures.
params._votedOracle: The address of the oracle voted as a publisher by the network.

subscribe(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

params.oracleAddr: the oracle address to subscribe to this coin pair.

unsubscribe(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

params.oracleAddr: the oracle address to subscribe to this coin pair.

devdoc.title: This contract provides an interface for feeding prices from oracles, and        get the current price. One contract must be instanced per supported coin pair,        and registered through OracleManager global contract.

canRemoveOracle(address).notice: Returns true if an oracle satisfies conditions to be removed from system.

changeIGovernor(address).notice: Change the contract's governor. Should be called through the old governance system

emergencyPublish(uint256).notice: Publish a price without signature validation (when there is an emergecy!!!).

getOracleRoundInfo(address).notice: Return round information for specific oracle

isSubscribed(address).notice: Returns true if an oracle is subscribed to this contract' coin pair

peek().notice: Return the current price, compatible with old MOC Oracle

subscribe(address).notice: subscribe an oracle to this coin pair , allowing it to be selected in rounds.

switchRound().notice: Switch contract context to a new round. With the objective of being a decentralized solution, this can be called by *anyone* if current round lock period is expired.

unsubscribe(address).notice: Unsubscribe an oracle from this coin pair , disallowing it to be selected in rounds.
